title: American Airlines pilot dies during flight, co-pilot lands plane
text:
American Airlines pilot dies during flight, co-pilot lands plane   
Oct 05, 2015 eTN   
American Airlines official said that the pilot of an American Airlines Airbus 320 died during early Monday flight from Phoenix to Boston, and the co-pilot landed the plane safely. The plane with 147 passengers and five crew members on board had to be diverted to Syracuse, NY. 
The airline has not yet released the pilot's name and age and did not specify the cause of death but said it was from "illness."
